Fix AOT compatibility warnings in the following non-serialization files in `/tmp/sv-905045ff8e9d40388ae1c6a5673bfb6f/before/`. Do NOT look at the `after/` directory.

## File 1: `ArmOperation.cs`
Lines 96-111 have `IsResource<T>()` method using `typeof(T).GetConstructor(...)` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` causing IL2087/IL2090.

Fix: Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` constraint to the `T` generic parameter of `IsResource<T>()`. You'll need `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` (check if already present).

Current code (lines 96-111):
```csharp
private static bool IsResource<T>() where T : notnull
{
    var isResource = typeof(T).GetConstructor(
                    BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance,
                    null,
                    CallingConventions.Any,
                    new Type[] { typeof(ArmClient), typeof(ResourceIdentifier) },
                    null) is not null;
    var obj = Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance, null, null, null);
    ...
}
```

Change the signature to:
```csharp
private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull
```

Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` if not already present.

## File 2: `GenericOperationSource.cs`
The class `GenericOperationSource<T>` uses `ModelReaderWriter.Read(response.Content, typeof(T))` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` causing IL2087.

Fix: Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the generic parameter `T` of the class definition.

Current line 16:
```csharp
internal class GenericOperationSource<T> : IOperationSource<T>
```

Change to:
```csharp
internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>
```

`using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` is already imported.

## File 3: `Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs`
Line 30 calls `builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration)` which has `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`.

Fix: Add `[RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming.")]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime.")]` to the `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` method.

Current (lines 27-31):
```csharp
public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
    where TBuilder : IAzureClientFactoryBuilderWithConfiguration<TConfiguration>
{
    return builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration);
}
```

Add the attributes before the method. Also add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` if not already present (it is imported on line 4).

## File 4: `ArmEnvironment.cs`
Line 80: `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` causes IL2026/IL3050.

Fix: Replace with manual JSON construction. ArmEnvironment has `Endpoint` (Uri) and `Audience` (string) and `DefaultScope` (string) properties. Build a JSON string manually:
```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    return $"{{\"Endpoint\":\"{Endpoint}\",\"Audience\":\"{Audience}\",\"DefaultScope\":\"{DefaultScope}\"}}";
}
```

Wait, that's not exactly the same output. `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` serializes all public properties. Let me use Utf8JsonWriter instead for safety:

```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    var buffer = new System.Buffers.ArrayBufferWriter<byte>();
    using (var writer = new Utf8JsonWriter(buffer))
    {
        writer.WriteStartObject();
        writer.WriteString("Endpoint", Endpoint.ToString());
        writer.WriteString("Audience", Audience);
        writer.WriteString("DefaultScope", DefaultScope);
        writer.WriteEndObject();
    }
    return System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(buffer.WrittenSpan);
}
```

Add `using System.Buffers;` and `using System.Text;` (check what's already imported). Also `using System.Text.Json;` should already be there.

Actually, looking at the current file, it has `using System.Text.Json;`. Let me be simpler and use the existing approach with Utf8JsonWriter but write it inline. Make sure to add `using System.Buffers;` if needed.

## File 5: `ArmClientOptions.cs`
Line 52: `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span)` causes IL2026/IL3050.

