Fix AOT compatibility warnings in the following non-serialization files in `/tmp/sv-905045ff8e9d40388ae1c6a5673bfb6f/before/`. Do NOT look at the `after/` directory.

## File 1: `ArmOperation.cs`
Lines 96-111 have `IsResource<T>()` method using `typeof(T).GetConstructor(...)` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` causing IL2087/IL2090.

Fix: Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` constraint to the `T` generic parameter of `IsResource<T>()`. You'll need `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` (check if already present).

Current code (lines 96-111):
```csharp
private static bool IsResource<T>() where T : notnull
{
    var isResource = typeof(T).GetConstructor(
                    BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance,
                    null,
                    CallingConventions.Any,
                    new Type[] { typeof(ArmClient), typeof(ResourceIdentifier) },
                    null) is not null;
    var obj = Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance, null, null, null);
    ...
}
```

Change the signature to:
```csharp
private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull
```

Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` if not already present.

## File 2: `GenericOperationSource.cs`
The class `GenericOperationSource<T>` uses `ModelReaderWriter.Read(response.Content, typeof(T))` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` causing IL2087.

Fix: Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the generic parameter `T` of the class definition.

Current line 16:
```csharp
internal class GenericOperationSource<T> : IOperationSource<T>
```

Change to:
```csharp
internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>
